organization.description: The GIS Support and Research Facility is a public computing facility established to support the use of geographic information system (GIS) technology at Iowa State University. The mission of the facility is to provide a high level GIS research support laboratory for students, faculty and staff as well as to provided GIS education and outreach to the ISU community and the state of Iowa.
organization.title: Iowa State University GIS Support and Research Facility
organization.name: iastate-edu

name: iowater-water-quality-monitoring-sites
notes: This coverage contains points representing monitoring locations on streams, lakes and ponds that have been registered by IOWATER monitors. IOWATER, Iowa's volunteer water monitoring program, supports a network of volunteers with onsite training workshops, standardized levels of testing, an online database to warehouse water quality data collected, and provides testing equipment. IOWATER monitors are instructed to use the 7.5' U.S. Geological Survey topographic maps available online through the Iowa Geographic Image Map Server (http://ortho.gis.iastate.edu) to generate UTM coordinates for their monitoring sites.
